reviews.review:
Well I went to see Star Wars 9 and my spoiler-free review is... no. Just... no.

The movie starts with a major plot point which is hinted at nowhere in 7 and 8 and completely undoes the triumphant ending of the original Star Wars trilogy.

Special effects--great, of course. Acting, serviceable, and nice job by Daisy Ridley as Rey.

One of the great things about Fury Road was the staging, you could tell how every battle was set and who was where doing what. This, the opposite. A muddled mess.

I would not know where to start. There was a time where Hollywood would give us what we did not expect with great story and character development. The problem with this entire trilogy is there was nothing clever about it. With so much great content in the Star Wars Cannon available, the writers went out on their own, I am not critical of that however, they failed terribly. They gave everyone what they wanted to see. Light Saber duels (Which I love) and great visuals (Second to none), but the story was just poorly written and completely uninspired. This last film reminded me of the final episode of Game of Thrones. We walked out like, "Really? That is it?" My feeling here is that Disney truly does not care because their focus is on producing much more inspired content on Disney+ where you can have months/seasons of character and story development, "Which I believe is a much better plan as Hollywood has just simply failed Star Wars Fans."
Great ending. Hit all the notes I needed it to.
the movie did not disappoint, I liked how the movie's story progressed and how it ended

Its okay but not the best ending. There were still some things that I rly just couldnt enjoy in terms of story etc. but its wayyyyyyyyyy better then TLJ. Its a good ending and I would set it on the same lvl as ROTS except for the graphics which of course are fcking awesome as always

The movie was great and while it was rushed and there was a lot to be expanded upon, it managed to give us something we can be satisfied with after veering away from what the last jedi was trying to build up.
Like always, Star Wars never disappoints!
Was slow to start but once it cleaned up everything from the last movie the second half of the movie was exactly what original trilogy fans were expecting after TFA.
I went in WANTING to hate this film. But it's good!!! A fun space adventure.
Visuals good, story falls apart though
